{"id": "1439751478792421416", "channel_id": "1439751478792421416", "type": 0, "author_id": "139343733714845697", "author_name": "satachan", "author_bot": false, "content": "As title stated, from what I have seen, we don't really have a Morimens Media kit or a content creator pack or anything like that, the most that we have right now is the character illustrations. \nHowever, I believe it would be beneficial for both players and content creator if we could have some of the blank images used for event banners so that it is easier for people to recognize guides and it would make content created for morimens have much better visual fidelity without people having to resort to AI cropping/remaking in game pictures, which is not very good.\n\nAddendum, Stuff like logos and UI elements(even relic icons) that are used in most guides are also very low resolution and incredibly hard to look at, I use the \"official\" logo of morimens for my videos and even that looks really bad, the resolution we get from google is absolute abyssmal, it's not a very good look for the game when we make content for it. (amatuerish)", "timestamp": "2025-11-16T22:58:21.833000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": "2025-11-17T02:29:08.988000+00:00", "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [{"emoji": "☝️", "emoji_id": null, "count": 5}], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1439751478792421416", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "✅「Answered」Is it possible to have some official  art of events and such for content creation?", "forum_channel_id": "1180845276823564288", "thread_tags": ["1361168939622727801", "1361169005435420785"]}
